Angle sum property of a triangle
Create a triangle using polygon tool
Draw a midpoint to any of the two sides of the triangle.
Find the angles ABC,BCA and CAB using the angle tool
Use the slider to create an angle \delta , min=0, max=180 degrees,increment=1 degrees
Use the rotate around point tool,and select the triangle(object) and the midpoint of the one 
      side of the triangle in anticlockwise direction,
      similarly repeat for the second side of the triangle in clockwise direction.
Start the animation.
\\End
https://www.geogebra.org/m/xber52re
